docs.abstract: On Friday, Mr. Altman was pushed out of the hot A.I. start-up he ran. But an intense pressure campaign and negotiations brought him back.
docs.snippet: On Friday, Mr. Altman was pushed out of the hot A.I. start-up he ran. But an intense pressure campaign and negotiations brought him back.
docs.lead_paragraph: One of the strangest episodes in the history of the tech industry ended as start-up events often do: with a party in San Francisco’s eclectic Mission District.

headline.main: Five Days of Chaos: How Sam Altman Returned to OpenAI
headline.print_headline: 5 Frantic Days: Inside a Battle To Run OpenAI

byline.original: By Cade Metz, Tripp Mickle, Mike Isaac, Karen Weise and Kevin Roose

docs.abstract: The tech giant moved quickly to hire Sam Altman and others after their abrupt departures from OpenAI, a key Microsoft partner.
docs.snippet: The tech giant moved quickly to hire Sam Altman and others after their abrupt departures from OpenAI, a key Microsoft partner.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft, the technology giant that ranks as one of the world’s most valuable companies, was shaken by the upheaval at OpenAI, the small but influential artificial intelligence start-up that developed the ChatGPT chatbot, before it found a way out of the turmoil that propelled its shares to a new high.

headline.main: Microsoft’s Stock Hits Record High After Hiring OpenAI Outcasts

docs.abstract: We spoke to the OpenAI founder just two days before he was ousted by his company’s board in a surprise coup. To him, the future seemed bright.
docs.snippet: We spoke to the OpenAI founder just two days before he was ousted by his company’s board in a surprise coup. To him, the future seemed bright.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Sam Altman, the chief executive of OpenAI, strolled into The Times’s San Francisco bureau last Wednesday morning, he looked carefree and relaxed — a happy mogul in an orange hoodie, riding a wave of success atop one of Silicon Valley’s hottest companies.

headline.main: ‘I Think We’re Heading Toward the Best World Ever’: An Interview With Sam Altman

docs.abstract: Big Tech is reeling from the ouster of Sam Altman at a leading A.I. start-up and his subsequent jump to Microsoft, moves that reset the power dynamic underpinning the sector.
docs.snippet: Big Tech is reeling from the ouster of Sam Altman at a leading A.I. start-up and his subsequent jump to Microsoft, moves that reset the power dynamic underpinning the sector.
docs.lead_paragraph: Over just three days, the landscape for artificial intelligence has been reshaped drastically. On Friday morning, Sam Altman was the C.E.O. of OpenAI, the leader in commercializing generative A.I. through ChatGPT. By Monday, he had not only been fired by his board — he had also joined Microsoft, the start-up’s biggest backer.

headline.main: The Shake-up at OpenAI Reshapes the Industry’s Global Order

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: The move capped a chaotic five days at the artificial intelligence company.
docs.snippet: The move capped a chaotic five days at the artificial intelligence company.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sam Altman was reinstated late Tuesday as OpenAI’s chief executive, the company said, successfully reversing his ouster by OpenAI’s board last week after a campaign waged by his allies, employees and investors.

headline.main: Sam Altman Is Reinstated as OpenAI’s Chief Executive

byline.original: By Cade Metz, Mike Isaac, Tripp Mickle, Karen Weise and Kevin Roose

docs.abstract: When summarizing facts, ChatGPT technology makes things up about 3 percent of the time, according to research from a new start-up. A Google system’s rate was 27 percent.
docs.snippet: When summarizing facts, ChatGPT technology makes things up about 3 percent of the time, according to research from a new start-up. A Google system’s rate was 27 percent.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the San Francisco start-up OpenAI unveiled its ChatGPT online chatbot late last year, millions were wowed by the humanlike way it answered questions, wrote poetry and discussed almost any topic. But most people were slow to realize that this new kind of chatbot often makes things up.

headline.main: Chatbots May ‘Hallucinate’ More Often Than Many Realize
headline.print_headline: A.I.-Powered Chatbots May ‘Hallucinate’ More Often Than Many Realized

docs.abstract: OpenAI’s intricate structure, which contributed to the ouster of Sam Altman, is complex by design.
docs.snippet: OpenAI’s intricate structure, which contributed to the ouster of Sam Altman, is complex by design.
docs.lead_paragraph: The future of OpenAI, whose ChatGPT kick-started an arms race in artificial intelligence, has grown even cloudier. A majority of its workers called on its board to resign after ousting Sam Altman as C.E.O. over how fast to commercialize its technology.

headline.main: Does A.I. Have an Inherent Governance Problem?

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Ravi Mattu, Bernhard Warner, Sarah Kessler, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni

docs.abstract: The fight over OpenAI was at least partly about dueling visions of artificial intelligence. One side clearly won out.
docs.snippet: The fight over OpenAI was at least partly about dueling visions of artificial intelligence. One side clearly won out.
docs.lead_paragraph: What happened at OpenAI over the past five days could be described in many ways: A juicy boardroom drama, a tug of war over one of America’s biggest start-ups, a clash between those who want A.I. to progress faster and those who want to slow it down.

headline.main: A.I. Belongs to the Capitalists Now
headline.print_headline: In Struggle Over Future of A.I., The Capitalist Perspective Wins

docs.abstract: Mr. Nadella moved fast to hire Sam Altman, who was pushed out of OpenAI on Friday, and asserted his company’s role in its partnership with the A.I. start-up.
docs.snippet: Mr. Nadella moved fast to hire Sam Altman, who was pushed out of OpenAI on Friday, and asserted his company’s role in its partnership with the A.I. start-up.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just two weeks ago, Microsoft’s Satya Nadella stood onstage next to OpenAI’s Sam Altman at the start-up’s conference in a former concert hall in San Francisco. Both wore black jeans, Mr. Altman in an army-green shirt and Mr. Nadella in navy casual.

headline.main: How Microsoft’s Satya Nadella Kept the ‘Best Bromance in Tech’ Alive

docs.abstract: Fired, then hired to the same post.
docs.snippet: Fired, then hired to the same post.
docs.lead_paragraph: In yet another head-spinning twist at OpenAI, Sam Altman was reinstated as the company’s chief executive on Tuesday night, a mere five days after the OpenAI board had fired him. The board will be overhauled and a new set of directors, including Bret Taylor and Lawrence Summers, will join.

headline.main: (Yet Another) Emergency Pod: Sam Altman Is Back

byline.original: By Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Rachel Cohn, Jen Poyant, Daniel Ramirez, Corey Schreppel and Dan Powell
